input:
Which of the following best explains the overall trend shown in the <image 1>?

Choices:
(A) Migrations to areas of Central Asia for resettlement
(B) The spread of pathogens across the Silk Road
(C) Invasions by Mongol tribes
(D) Large-scale famine due to crop failures
output:
(B) The spread of pathogens across the Silk Road.

The simultaneous, long-term population declines in both the Roman and Han regions are best explained by pandemics transmitted along interregional trade routes (e.g., the Antonine/other plagues in the Roman world and epidemic outbreaks in late Han China), which reduced populations across Eurasia.
